Problem Statement - The challenge with Commercial Banks are the diverse bank accounts which may vary as per demographics such as salaried persons or pensioners. The time gap between the intimation of death of a customer to the bank and the steps to be taken for suspending the account creates a significant window for unethical transactions in the deceased account. It is a practical challenge being faced by the financial institutions despite the existing preventive steps at present and creates operational and compliance risks for financial institutions.
